Pronotum : Trapezoidal; robust collar clearly longer than width of tibiae. Anterior lobe of pronotum and collar very densely punctate; posterior lobe sparsely punctate with larger punctures (
Fig. 1
). Transverse furrow deep, posterior and anterior (with collar) lobes of similar length. Anterior lobe dorsally convex, posterior lobe rather flat. Lateral margin carinate from behind collar to humeral angles, not very broad, and not broader at level of tranverse furrow than behind it. Lateral margins sinuate, flaring behind transverse furrow.

Male genitalia : Pygophore (
Fig. 4
) round with relatively broad opening and short pubescence. Paramere (
Fig. 9–10
) slender, with slightly curved apex and broad, somewhat angular inner projection, with sparse short pubescence.
